question:
Consider the following code. How many threads are created and running concurrently (at the same time) when the main method executes?

```java
public class Challenge {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Thread t1 = new Thread(() -> System.out.println("One"));
        Thread t2 = new Thread(() -> System.out.println("Two"));
        Thread t3 = new Thread(() -> System.out.println("Three"));

        t1.start();
        t2.run(); // Note: run() is called directly, not start()
        t3.start();
    }
}
```
